B Implementation details
For the implementation of the approach developed during this research, two principal sources files have been written in the R language, using the RWeka packages and executed in a R platform (see section 2.5).
The first one is used for the representation of all the differents plots shown previously (and more). Given a dataset or a set of datasets and a set of machine learning models (J48, IBk, and SMO in this case), this program first splits each dataset into train and test parts, then trains the train data with each model; after that it proceeds to the reframing of the model and evaluates each reframed model. the result of the accuracy is then represented in a graph, as the trade-off of misclassification and test cost, the JROC convex hull graphs. The result of the approximation of the methods defined in section 4 can also be shown.
